# Adventure Game Console Application

## Description
This is a simple console-based adventure game implemented in C#.  
The application allows the user to create a hero character and perform an attack based on the hero type.  

The program demonstrates the use of:

- Variables
- Operators
- Loops
- Conditional statements
- Functions
- Classes and objects

## Hero Class

The `Hero` class represents a hero in the adventure game and has the following properties:

- `Name` – the name of the hero
- `Type` – the type of hero (mage, warrior, monk, ninja)

The class also has a method `Attack()` that displays a message based on the hero type:

| Hero Type | Attack Message       |
|-----------|--------------------|
| mage      | used magic         |
| warrior   | used sword         |
| monk      | used martial arts  |
| ninja     | used shuriken      |

